[div class=p 
	"Editors will see an small edit button on the bottom right hand side of a movie module.  This allows them to access the movie edit page.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[code 
		"Description
	]code
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Edits the movie description text.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[code 
		"Headers
	]code
	$LF
	"Ability to edit the Player name, Platform, Game name, Game version, Branch name, ROM filename and the "Hacked movie" status.  Accessed from the Edit info button.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Do not change the player without good reason (and admin approval).
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Follow the 
		(__wikiLink|href=/PublisherGuidelines|implicitdisplaytext=Publisher Guidelines)
		" regarding giving the proper Game Name, Version, Branch, ROM Name, and Movie filenames.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" The "hacked game or otherwise impure movie" checkbox places the movie in the Concept/Demos category.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	[code 
		"Tags
	]code
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Ability to edit the movie categories (such as "Heavy Glitch Abuse").  Clicking "edit classes" brings up a list of available Tags.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"When editing movie tags, follow the 
	(__wikiLink|href=/MovieTagGuidelines|implicitdisplaytext=Movie Tag Guidelines)
	".
	$LF
]div
